        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 18 at 3:59PM MDT until August 18 at 4:30PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 358 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 11 miles southeast of Thurman to 6 miles east of Hugo,
moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Mesonet. A station north of Flagler recently reported a
wind gust of 60 mph.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

These severe storms will be near...
Flagler around 410 PM MDT.

This includes Interstate 70 in Colorado between mile markers 391 and
425.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
